<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1169">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Infante</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chilean
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Cape May, N.
                                    J.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have had the honor to receive
                            the note in which your excellency indicates the advisability of duly
                            observing the customary naval rules in case of blockade each time that a
                            neutral vessel <pb facs="1257" n="1161" xml:id="pg_1161"/> of war may
                            desire to enter or to leave a port blockaded by the American naval
                            forces. Your excellency suggests certain particular observances relative
                            to the port of Habana.</p>
                        <p>For the due observance of these rules I have hastened to communicate to
                            my Government your excellency’s above-mentioned note.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself of this occasion to renew to your excellency the
                            assurances of my highest consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Infante.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>